description: Voters punish President Macron's party, though turnout was at record lows amid the pandemic.
title: France municipal elections: Greens score gains in second round
title_page: France municipal elections: Greens score gains in second round - BBC News
maintext: One of their candidates took the city of Perpignan in the south - the largest city the far-right has won since the 1990s. Ms Le Pen declared a "real victory" on Sunday.
